## 1. Overview of Assessment Objectives

| AO | What It Tests | What to Do |
|----|---------------|------------|
| **AO1** | Knowledge & Understanding | Describe, outline, identify, state theories/studies/concepts with key terminology |
| **AO2** | Application | Apply psychological knowledge to a novel scenario/stem — do NOT just quote the stem; explain WHY the behaviour fits the theory |
| **AO3** | Analysis & Evaluation | Evaluate using PEEL (Point, Evidence, Explain, Link) — strengths, limitations, methodological issues, supporting/contradicting research, real-world applications, ethical issues |

